  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nCurrently, FC plugin doesn't have a chance to update attached volume's devicePath into volume object.\r\nWe discussed this at the following thread but this proposal wasn't accepted.\r\n- https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/54264\r\n- https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/56803\r\n\r\nIf the volumeMode is Block, we have these three main operations during block volume teardown path, but  all of them fail since devicePath isn't passed to these operations.\r\n- TearDownDevice()\r\n- Remove loopback device\r\n- Check device open status\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nSuccessfully complete these operations during teardown path.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n- Create pod with FC volume which has volumeMode=Block\r\n- Delete pod with FC volume\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n```\r\nk8sbuild-master mtanino% k version                                                                                                                                    [~/sample/storage/fc_loop/block/block]\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"10+\", GitVersion:\"v1.10.0-alpha.0.856+7320a45fc2ab63-dirty\", GitCommit:\"7320a45fc2ab6350018d4884afd39514eb596dc2\", GitTreeState:\"dirty\", BuildDate:\"2017-12-12T23:38:59Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.2\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"10+\", GitVersion:\"v1.10.0-alpha.0.856+7320a45fc2ab63-dirty\", GitCommit:\"7320a45fc2ab6350018d4884afd39514eb596dc2\", GitTreeState:\"dirty\", BuildDate:\"2017-12-13T16:13:19Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.2\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n```\r\n- Install tools: local-cluster-up.sh\r\n",
